'''领土'''（{{lang-en|Territory}}），亦稱'''疆域'''，是指[[主权国家|主权国家]]所管辖的[[地区|地区]]範圍<ref>{{cite book|last1=Biersteker|first1=Thomas|last2=Weber|first2=Cynthia |title=State Sovereignty as Social Construct|url=http://books.google.com.au/books?id=qy97O2Eon0gC|series=Cambridge Studies in International Relations|volume=46|year=1996|publisher=Cambridge University Press|ISBN=9780521565998}}</ref>，通常包括一个该国[[边界|国界]]（[[邊境|邊境]]）内的[[陆地|陆地]]（即[[领土#領陸|领陆]]）、[[內水|內水]]（包括[[河流|河流]]、[[湖泊|湖泊]]、[[内海|内海]]），以及它们的[[底床|底床]]、[[底土|底土]]和上空（[[领空|领空]]），有时亦会包括[[领海|领海]]。<ref name=Krasner>{{cite book|pages=6–12|url=http://books.google.com/books?id=ISqwQIBQff4C&lpg=PA7&pg=PA7|title=Problematic Sovereignty: Contested Rules and Political Possibilities|isbn=9780231121798|author1=Krasner|first1=Professor Stephen D.|year=2001}}</ref> 

領土與[[國家|國家]]存亡有密切關係，因為領土是[[国家|国家]]的一部份，形成國家的必要[[條件|條件]]，國家行使[[主權|主權]]的地域及顯示出國家獨有的主權的方式。<ref name="britannica">{{cite encyclopedia|encyclopedia=[[Encyclopædia_Britannica|Encyclopædia Britannica]]|title=sovereignty (politics)|url=http://www.britannica.com/EBchecked/topic/557065/sovereignty|accessdate=5 August 2010|archive-date=2015-05-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150503104728/http://www.britannica.com/EBchecked/topic/557065/sovereignty|dead-url=no}}</ref>

此外，領土的英語對應詞「{{lang|en|territory}}」亦可用來做為[[行政區劃|行政區劃]]的類型，例如[[加拿大行政区划#地區/领地|加拿大的「地區」]]。

==起源==
領土的起源可追溯至公元前，當時[[人|人類]]逐漸由[[游牧|游牧]]轉至[[农业|農耕]]，並由[[氏族|氏族]]轉至[[部落|部落]]，擁有獨自的[[領袖|首領]]。部落擁有自己的農田、活動範圍，且[[社會階層|階級]]制度開始形成，漸漸形成[[勢力範圍|勢力範圍]]。勢力範圍是一個部落的管控地區，領土的基本概念形成。後來，勢力範圍便轉變成領土，部落轉變成國家，首領轉變成[[皇帝|皇帝]]或[[君主|君主]]，領土正式形成，成為國家的一個象徵。<ref name="britannica"/>

領土在初時定義模糊，且疆界不清，難以考察國家的實際領土。直至近幾百年，領土疆界才逐漸清晰。<ref name="max-seydel">{{Cite journal | url = http://books.google.com/?id=Gl9JAAAAIAAJ&pg=PA80&dq=%22there+is+no+law+without+a+sovereign%22+Seydel | title = A society of states: Or, Sovereignty, independence, and equality in a league of nations | author1 = Stallybrass | first1 = William Teulon Swan | year = 1918}}</ref>

==國家領土==
[[File:Geo_land2.PNG|thumb]]
國家擁有的領土理論上是不可分割、不可侵犯的。<ref name="talmon">{{cite book|last=Talmon|first=Stefan|title=Recognition of Governments in International Law|url=http://books.google.com.au/books?id=scc8EboiJX8C&pg=PA50|series=Oxford Monographs in International Law Series|year=1998|publisher=Oxford University Press|isbn=9780198265733|page=50}}</ref>國家在其領土上有完全的主權和管轄權，且其他國家理論上無權干涉。<ref>Newton, Kenneth. Foundations of comparative politics: democracies of the modern world. Cambridge: Cambridge University Press, 2005.</ref><ref>{{cite web | title = C-26/62 ''Van Gend en Loos v. Nederlanse Administratie Der Belastingen'' | url = http://eur-lex.europa.eu/LexUriServ/LexUriServ.do?uri=CELEX:61962J0026:EN:HTML | work = Eur-Lex | accessdate = 2007-01-19 | archive-date = 2007-03-21 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20070321191046/http://eur-lex.europa.eu/LexUriServ/LexUriServ.do?uri=CELEX:61962J0026:EN:HTML | dead-url = no }}</ref>領土大小也象徵著國家的強弱，如冷戰時兩大國[[美国|美国]]與[[苏联|苏联]]也是領土超過9,000,000平方公里的國家。又如殖民時代英法等歐洲列強殖民領土都象徵帝國強弱。<ref>{{cite book|url=http://books.google.com/books?id=eVPQWWqHbi8C&pg=PA106&lpg=PA106&dq=%22try+to+be+one+of+three%22+%22five+great+powers%22&source=web&ots=RTFf5BgiqV&sig=GIpRg4plsUbafYB-F4S5xnkPluw&hl=en&sa=X&oi=book_result&resnum=2&ct=result |title=Peace, War, and the European Powers, 1814–1914 |publisher=Books.google.com |date= |accessdate=2011-06-12}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|url=http://books.google.com/books?id=DkN6M2mvh9EC&pg=PA86&lpg=PA86&dq=%22be+one+of+three%22+%22five+great+powers%22&source=web&ots=94EEpqiR5I&sig=rbQ08zhwPnJQx3GaoHlNE79aQ74&hl=en&sa=X&oi=book_result&resnum=5&ct=result |title=Ideology and International Relations in the Modern World |publisher=Books.google.com |date= |accessdate=2011-06-12}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.sscnet.ucla.edu/polisci/faculty/trachtenberg/cv/SCHROEDE.doc |title=The Transformation of European Politics, 1763–1848 |date= |accessdate=2011-06-12 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110608075917/http://www.sscnet.ucla.edu/polisci/faculty/trachtenberg/cv/SCHROEDE.doc |archivedate=2011-06-08 }}</ref>領土擁有權糾紛甚會直接導致戰爭，致使國家滅亡。<ref>[http://jcr.sagepub.com/cgi/content/abstract/32/1/87 Power Transitions as the cause of war].</ref>

每個國家都擁有不同大小的領土，其現今的領土視乎不同因素，如地理、歷史、民族等。<ref>{{cite book|last=Mälksoo|first=Lauri|title=Illegal Annexation and State Continuity: The Case of the Incorporation of the Baltic States by the USSR|year=2003|publisher=M. Nijhoff Publishers|isbn=9041121773|page=193|url=http://books.google.com.au/books?id=p5w6AQAAIAAJ}}</ref>

沒有領土的國家稱之為[[流亡政府|流亡政府]]，如二战时期[[夏爾·戴高樂|戴高乐]]领导的[[自由法國|自由法國]]政府等等。<ref name='nolan'>{{cite book|last=Nolan|first=Cathal J.|title=The Greenwood Encyclopedia of International Relations|url=http://books.google.com.au/books?id=FMJ8KP8i3v0C&pg=PA1559|volume=Volume 4|year=2002|publisher=Greenwood Publishing Group|page=1559}}</ref><ref>[http://wordnetweb.princeton.edu/perl/webwn?s=government-in-exile Princeton University WordNet]</ref>而[[聖座|聖座]]亦是一個典型例子。聖座於1870年[[教宗国|教宗国]]被吞併至1929年因簽訂《[[拉特朗条约|拉特朗条约]]》而成立[[梵蒂冈|梵蒂冈]]期間都是一個沒有任何領土的流亡政府。<ref>Robert Araujo and John Lucal, Papal Diplomacy and the Quest for Peace, the Vatican and International Organizations from the early years to the League of Nations, Sapienza Press (2004), ISBN 978-1-932589-01-6, p. 16. ''See also'' James Crawford, The Creation of States in International Law, (1979) p. 154.</ref>

